title: Google has probably ended official updates for the 2018 Pixel 3 and Pixel 3 XL
content:
The Pixel 3 and Pixel 3 XL were released in October 2018, and remained Google’s flagship phones until the Pixel 4 series arrived to replace them around a year later. Even though October 2018 might seem like ages ago, it was only a little over three years ago, and now the Pixel 3 series has

The post Google has probably ended official updates for the 2018 Pixel 3 and Pixel 3 XL appeared first on xda-developers.
description: The Pixel 3 and Pixel 3 XL are likely done receiving official updates after this month's February 2022 security patch
